## Development Notes

### Testing Requirements
- Cross-browser: Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge (mobile & desktop)
- Device testing: iPhone SE, iPhone 14, Pixel 7, Samsung Galaxy, iPad
- Screen reader testing: VoiceOver, TalkBack
- AMP validation on every page
- Lighthouse audits before delivery
- When uncertain: ask questions before coding.

### Code Quality
- Semantic HTML5
- BEM or utility-first CSS methodology
- Commented code for complex sections
- Consistent formatting (Prettier)
- Valid W3C HTML
- Do not implement speculative or extra features.
- Confirm completion only after verifying correctness, performance, and compliance.

---

## Prompt Summary

> Build a mobile-first, AMP-compatible legal aid intake portal called MyLegalAid. The site connects people seeking legal help with appropriate providers. The site performs all the intake and eligibility requirements to free up the provider to focus on providing world-class service. This also allows a person seeking legal aid assistance to complete a single intake application for all providers rather than going through the process of completing an intake application for each provider. The intake application will be highly automated and easy and efficient for the client to use - it will utilize conversational AI, text messaging and online tools that are all mobile friendly. including: (1) SEO optimized — SEO optimized for both search bots and AI to maximize the likelihood that a person looking online for legal assistance will be referred to the site; (2) Conversational AI client portal — clients can speak with a human-like AI agent 24/7 in multiple languages to complete an intake application, tracking cases, and access additional resources; (3) Client follow-up — automated followup with clients for intake completion, service satisfaction, etc.; (4) Secure online provider portal — dashboard, referral management, profile/criteria settings, real-time utilization of profile settings. Use Tailwind CSS and Bootstrap, prioritize 90% mobile usage, implement full SEO with Schema.org markup, ensure WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility, and create a "calm authority" design aesthetic with trust blue and warm gold colors. Phase 1 is a functional prototype with stellar UX and realistic interactions, deferring backend integration to a later phase. All images should feel authentic and hopeful, never generic stock.
